## **1. Executive Summary** 

Verdict: **Strong delivery overall, but one structural item still blocks the rest of the work from being seen by visitors.** The April 2026 audit produced 54 findings; the Phase 2 plan (May 2026) flagged 5 buckets of remaining cleanup. Most of those have now been delivered. Specifically, the RWF 7,000 government-fee error is fully removed, the homepage now opens with an investor-focused hero plus the "Muraho" welcome message, the FAQ has been expanded well beyond plan, and the dedicated landing pages exist with on-brand investor copy. 

**Two items remain unresolved and one is a known scope deferral.** (1) The main-navigation gap is still open — the Services dropdown does not expose the five dedicated landing pages, the homepage service cards still link to the legacy generic pages, and there is no dedicated gold "Book Free Consultation" CTA button in the header. (2) The /explore-rwanda and /gallery URLs continue to serve identical HTML, which is a duplicate-content SEO risk. (3) Reservations is intentionally deferred — Section 5 covers the recommended architecture for that build. 

## **Scoreboard** 

Of 12 Phase-2 line items verified on-site today: **8 DONE** · **2 PARTIAL** · **2 OPEN (nav, duplicate page)** 

